Protogenes at Rhodes. Protogenes was held in low esteem by his fellow-countrymen‚ as is usual with home products, and, when Apelles asked him what price he set on some works he had finished, he had mentioned some small sum, but Apelles made him an offer of fifty talents for them, and spread it about that he was buying them with the intention of selling them as works of his own. This device aroused the people of Rhodes to appreciate the artist. and Apelles only parted with the pictures to them at an enhanced price.
